## API Endpoints and Implementation

### SDK Implementation

```javascript
// Installation
npm install @amplitude/engagement-browser

// Basic initialization
import { boot } from '@amplitude/engagement-browser';

boot({
  client: {
    apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY',
    configuration: {
      serverUrl: 'https://api.amplitude.com',
      serverZone: 'US'
    }
  }
});

// With third-party analytics
import { boot, forwardEvent } from '@amplitude/engagement-browser';

boot({
  client: {
    apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY',
    configuration: {
      serverUrl: 'https://api.amplitude.com',
      serverZone: 'US'
    }
  }
});

// Forward events from third-party analytics
analytics.on('track', event => {
  forwardEvent({
    event_type: event.event,
    event_properties: event.properties
  });
});

// Set theme mode
import { setThemeMode } from '@amplitude/engagement-browser';
setThemeMode('dark');

// Add callbacks
import { addCallback } from '@amplitude/engagement-browser';
addCallback('guideViewed', (guide) => {
  console.log('Guide viewed:', guide);
});
```

### Localization Configuration

```javascript
// SDK initialization with locale
boot({
  client: {
    apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY',
    configuration: {
      serverUrl: 'https://api.amplitude.com',
      serverZone: 'US'
    }
  },
  locale: 'fr-FR' // Set user's locale
});
```

### Preview Mode Testing

Preview mode can be accessed through the UI or via URL parameters:
```
https://your-site.com/?gsPreview=true&gsPreviewId=YOUR_GUIDE_ID
```

### CloudFront Proxy Configuration

For environments where direct access to Amplitude domains is blocked, a CloudFront distribution can be configured with:

- Origin 1: cdn.amplitude.com (for static assets)
- Origin 2: gs.amplitude.com (for API traffic)

SDK initialization with proxy:
```javascript
boot({
  client: {
    apiKey: 'YOUR_API_KEY',
    configuration: {
      serverUrl: 'https://your-cloudfront-distribution.com',
      cdnUrl: 'https://your-cloudfront-distribution.com'
    }
  }
});
```